1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":13,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Deedgefield was born about 1277, in Witchingham, Norfolk, England. She married Richard Germain de Berney in 1291, in Witchingham, Norfolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died about 1309, in Norfolk, England, at the age of 34, and was buried in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1277–about 1309":"umbes 1277–umbes 1309","1273–1325":"1273–1325","1293–Female":"1293–Surnud","1294–1382":"1294–1382","1295–1374":"1295–1374","1297–1332":"1297–1332","1277–1309":"1277–1309","about 1294":"umbes 1294","1297":"1297","1374":"1374","1295":"1295","1273":"1273","1382":"1382","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","about 1309":"umbes 1309","1325":"1325","1277":"1277","1332":"1332","about 1277":"umbes 1277","1309":"1309","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England","Saint Michael Coslany, Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Nor